%pyspark

import datetime as dt
import pyspark.sql.functions as f
#from dateutil import tz
from pyspark.sql.types import DateType, StringType, IntegerType
from pyspark.sql.window import Window


# Setup functions and retrieve data

# get today's date for the directory structure to look in
dirDate = dt.datetime.strftime(dt.date.today() - dt.timedelta(days=1), '%Y/%m/%d')

print ("Searching for directory date: ", dirDate)


# Create a UDF to covert date string to date object
changeToDate = f.udf(lambda x: dt.datetime.strptime(x, "%m/%d/%y"), DateType())

#def stringToDate(val):
#    try:
#      result = dt.datetime.strptime(x, "%m/%d/%Y")
#    exception:
#      result = dt.datetime.strptime(x, "%m/%d/%y")
#      
#    return result
    

# Create a function to extract dated column names as a array of strings
def getDateColumns(cols):
    dates = []
    for val in cols:
        if '/' in val:
            dates.append(val)
    return dates
    
# load the data into their respective data frames
covidCaseDf = sqlContext.read.csv("file:////opt/data/in/usafacts/" + dirDate + "/covid_confirmed_usafacts.csv",header="true")
covidPopulationDf = sqlContext.read.csv("file:////opt/data/in/usafacts/" + dirDate + "/covid_county_population_usafacts.csv", header="true")
covidDeathsDf = sqlContext.read.csv("file:////opt/data/in/usafacts/" + dirDate + "/covid_deaths_usafacts.csv", header="true")

%pyspark


# Clean up state population data
covidPopulationDf = covidPopulationDf.withColumn("population", covidPopulationDf.population.cast(IntegerType()))
statePopulationDf = covidPopulationDf.groupBy('State').sum('population')
statePopulationDf = statePopulationDf.withColumnRenamed('sum(population)', 'Population')
statePopulationDf = statePopulationDf.withColumn('Population (1K)', statePopulationDf.Population/1000)
statePopulationDf = statePopulationDf.withColumn('Population (10K)', statePopulationDf.Population/10000)
statePopulationDf = statePopulationDf.withColumn('Population (100K)', statePopulationDf.Population/100000)
statePopulationDf = statePopulationDf.withColumn('Population (M)', statePopulationDf.Population/1000000)


# Fix time fields for the date column

datesStr = []

## not sure which is better date as a string or date as an object
## create both arrays and figure it out as we go
#for name in covidCaseDf.columns:
#    if '/' in name:
#        dates.append(datetime.datetime.strptime(name, "%m/%d/%y"))
#        datesStr.append(name)

# Get the dates from header as a array
datesStr = getDateColumns(covidCaseDf.columns)
print("Date String is: ", datesStr)

# to store date string value in records
df = covidCaseDf.withColumn("Date", f.array([f.lit(x) for x in datesStr]))

# explode the array so every record has a date column/value
df = df.withColumn('Date', f.explode(df.Date))

# initialize Count to dataframe
df = df.withColumn('Count', f.lit(0))
for x in datesStr:
    df = df.withColumn("Count", f.when( df.Date == x, f.col(x).cast(IntegerType())).otherwise(df.Count))

df = df.withColumn('Date', changeToDate(df.Date))

# drop the date columns that were originally assigned
df = df.drop(*datesStr)


ccaseDf = df
ccaseDf = ccaseDf.drop('countyFIPS', 'stateFIPS')
ccaseDf = ccaseDf.withColumnRenamed('Count', 'CaseCount').withColumnRenamed('County Name', 'CountyName')
ccaseDf.printSchema()

#print "distinct date and datesStr: ", df.select('Date').distinct().count()

# process covid death data

print "covid death rec count: ", covidDeathsDf.count()

datesStr = getDateColumns(covidDeathsDf.columns)

# to store date string value in records
df = covidDeathsDf.withColumn("Date", f.array([f.lit(x) for x in datesStr]))

# explode the array so every record has a date column/value

# initialize Count to dataframe
df = df.withColumn('Count', f.lit(0))
for x in datesStr:
    df = df.withColumn("Count", f.when( df.Date == x, f.col(x).cast(IntegerType())).otherwise(df.Count))

print "done for loop"

df = df.withColumn('Date', changeToDate(df.Date))
#df.select('State', 'County Name', 'Date', 'Count').show(10)

print "changed date"

df.printSchema()

cdeathDf = df

cdeathDf.printSchema()

print "file recs: ", covidCaseDf.count()
print "df recs: ", df.count()

print "covid population rec count: ", covidPopulationDf.count()

%pyspark


# prepare the usa fact data so we have all the data maintained in a single record.
# so when lookign up a state and county we can get the cases, deaths, and population for that day.

# Build knowledge base

kbDf = ccaseDf.join(cdeathDf, ['State', 'CountyName', 'Date']).join(cpopulationDf, ['State', 'CountyName'])

kbAggDf = kbDf.groupBy('State', 'Date').sum('CaseCount', 'DeathCount').sort('State', 'Date')

# fix the column names
kbAggDf = kbAggDf.withColumnRenamed('sum(CaseCount)', 'CaseCount').withColumnRenamed('sum(DeathCount)', 'DeathCount')

# add population by state data
kbAggDf = kbAggDf.join(statePopulationDf, 'State')

%pyspark

kbAggDf.printSchema()

kbAggDf.filter(kbAggDf.State == "MD").select(f.max(kbAggDf.Date)).show()

#print kbAggDf.filter( (kbAggDf.State == "MD") & (kbAggDf.Date == '2020-08-15') ).groupBy('State').agg(f.sum('CaseCount')).select('State', 'Date', 'Population', 'CaseCount').show(40, False)

#x = kbAggDf.filter( (kbAggDf.State == "MD") & (kbAggDf.Date == '2020-08-15') ).groupBy('State').agg(f.sum(kbAggDf.CaseCount).alias('totalCaseCountState'))

x = kbAggDf.filter( (kbAggDf.State == "MD") & (kbAggDf.Date == '2020-08-15') ).groupBy('State', 'Date').agg(f.max('Date'), f.sum(kbAggDf.CaseCount).alias('totalCaseCountState'))

y = kbAggDf.join(x, ['State', 'Date'])

y = kbAggDf.join(x, ['State', 'Date'])
y.show(40, False)

%pyspark


# Time to track daily changes within each state group of covid-19 and death rates

# derive daily delta for case and death count

deltaWindow = Window.partitionBy("State").orderBy("Date")
caseDeltaWindow = Window.partitionBy().orderBy("State", "Date", "CaseCount")
deathDeltaWindow = Window.partitionBy().orderBy("State", "Date", "DeathCount")

xdf = kbAggDf.withColumn('prevCaseCount', f.lag(kbAggDf.CaseCount).over(deltaWindow))
xdf = xdf.withColumn('prevDeathCount', f.lag(xdf.DeathCount).over(deltaWindow))

xdf = xdf.withColumn('CaseCountDelta', f.when(f.isnull(xdf.CaseCount - xdf.prevCaseCount), 0).otherwise(xdf.CaseCount - xdf.prevCaseCount))
xdf = xdf.withColumn('DeathCountDelta', f.when(f.isnull(xdf.DeathCount - xdf.prevDeathCount), 0).otherwise(xdf.DeathCount - xdf.prevDeathCount))

xdf.printSchema()


#
# State Reporting COVID-19 Cases and Deaths
#

# Group: State
# Values: CaseCount
# Values: DeathCount

rptDf = xdf.drop('prevCaseCount', 'prevDeathCount').filter((xdf.Date > f.lit('2020-03-11')) & (xdf.State.isin(['MD'])) ).sort('Date')

print ("Rate Of Cases Found")
print ("COVID-19 Cases")
z.show(rptDf) 
print ("COVID-19 Deaths")
z.show(rptDf)
print ("Table of Data")
z.show(rptDf)

# Values: DeathCountDelta

print("Daily Differences")

%pyspark


#
# Report to the county level
#


kbDf.printSchema()

#countyRpt = kbDf.filter( (kbDf.Date > f.lit('2020-03-11')) & (kbDf.State == 'MD') & (kbDf.CountyName.isin(['Baltimore City', 'Baltimore County', 'Howard County']))).sort('State', 'CountyName', 'Date')

kbAggDf = kbDf.groupBy('State', 'CountyName', 'Date').sum('CaseCount', 'DeathCount').sort('State', 'CountyName', 'Date')

# fix the column names
kbAggDf = kbAggDf.withColumnRenamed('sum(CaseCount)', 'CaseCount').withColumnRenamed('sum(DeathCount)', 'DeathCount')

# add population by state data
kbAggDf = kbAggDf.join(statePopulationDf, 'State')

# add county population by state data
countyPopulationDf = covidPopulationDf
countyPopulationDf = countyPopulationDf.withColumnRenamed('County Name', 'CountyName')
countyPopulationDf = countyPopulationDf.withColumnRenamed('population', 'CountyPopulation')
countyPopulationDf = countyPopulationDf.withColumn('CountyPopulation (1K)', countyPopulationDf.CountyPopulation/1000)
countyPopulationDf = countyPopulationDf.withColumn('CountyPopulation (10K)', countyPopulationDf.CountyPopulation/10000)
countyPopulationDf = countyPopulationDf.withColumn('CountyPopulation (100K)', countyPopulationDf.CountyPopulation/100000)
countyPopulationDf = countyPopulationDf.withColumn('CountyPopulation (M)', countyPopulationDf.CountyPopulation/1000000)

# Remove redundant strings from column values
# countyPopulationDf = countyPopulationDf.withColumn('CountyName', f.regexp_replace('CountyName', ' County', ''))

countyAggDf = kbAggDf.join(countyPopulationDf, ['State', 'CountyName'])


deltaWindow = Window.partitionBy("State", "CountyName").orderBy("Date")

countyRpt = countyAggDf.withColumn('prevCaseCount', f.lag(countyAggDf.CaseCount).over(deltaWindow))
countyRpt = countyRpt.withColumn('prevDeathCount', f.lag(countyRpt.DeathCount).over(deltaWindow))

countyRpt = countyRpt.withColumn('CaseCountDelta', f.when(f.isnull(countyRpt.CaseCount - countyRpt.prevCaseCount), 0).otherwise(countyRpt.CaseCount - countyRpt.prevCaseCount))
countyRpt = countyRpt.withColumn('DeathCountDelta', f.when(f.isnull(countyRpt.DeathCount - countyRpt.prevDeathCount), 0).otherwise(countyRpt.DeathCount - countyRpt.prevDeathCount))


countyRpt.printSchema()

countyRptDf = countyRpt.filter( (countyRpt.State == 'MD')\
    & (countyRpt.Date > f.lit('2020-03-11'))\
    & (countyRpt.CountyName.isin(['Howard County']))  )
#    & (countyRpt.CountyName.isin(['Baltimore City', 'Baltimore County', 'Howard County', 'Carroll County', 'Anne Arundel County']))  )

print ("County Case and Death Rates")
z.show(countyRptDf)

print ("County Case and Death Deltas")
z.show(countyRptDf)
